I'm always on the lookout for a salad that's fun and flavorful.¬†ü•ó Whether that's adding caramelized onions, creamy dressings, spiced nuts, or some punchy chopped fruit.¬†While delicious, Caesar salads are drowned in dressing and covered with cheese.¬†So I‚Äôve partnered with @wholefoods in the spirit of the the New Year to show you #HowIJanuary and I‚Äôve remixed this classic salad to help you enjoy it in a new and delicious way. I pared down your typical Caesar to still offer all that creamy goodness with a vegan dressing, some gluten-free croutons, and I swapped in shaved brussels sprouts because they're a good source of fiber and hold up in the fridge for a few days. Follow the link in my profile to find more gluten-free options for you to add to your meals!¬†#Sponsored #MakesMeWhole

Here's the recipe below:

RECIPE:
Brussels Sprouts Caesar Salad: -2lbs. brussels sprouts, shaved thin on a mandolin or with a sharp knife
- drizzle extra virgin olive oil
- squeeze lemon juice
- fat pinch salt
-1 ripe avocado, sliced
- gluten-free croutons (optional)
- walnuts shaved on a microplane, to garnish (optional) 
Dressing: -1/2 c Plain Kite Hill Greek-style yogurt
-1 tablespoon lemon juice
-1 tablespoon apple cider vinegar
-1 1/2 tablespoons nutritional yeast
-2 teaspoons Dijon mustard
-2 teaspoons capers
-1 clove garlic, grated on a microplane
-Salt & pepper, to taste
-1/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil 
1. Toss shaved brussels sprouts with the olive oil, lemon juice, and salt. ¬†Use your hands and mix everything together for about 1 minute. ¬†Set aside.
2. From our family to yours, Happy Holidays üéÑüí´‚òÉÔ∏è#familytotable ‚ú®
Cranberry Coffee Crumb Cake
- 1 cup brown rice flour
- 1/2 cup oat flour
- 1 teaspoon baking powder
- 1/2 teaspoon baking soda
- 1 teaspoon ground cinnamon
- 1/2 teaspoon ground nutmeg
- 1/2 teaspoon fine sea salt
- 4 tablespoons unsalted Country Crock baking sticks
- 2/3 cup coconut sugar - 2 large eggs
- 1 teaspoon pure vanilla extract
- 1/2 cup dairy-free cultured yogurt
- 1 cup whole cranberry sauce
‚ú®
Crumb Topping:
- 1/2 cup brown rice flour
- 1/3 cup old fashioned rolled oats
-1/3 cup coconut sugar
-1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon
-1/8 teaspoon fine sea salt
- 4 tablespoons unsalted Country Crock baking sticks
‚ú®
Method 
1. Preheat oven to 350F, oil an 8-inch springform pan and lime the bottom with parchment, set aside. 
2. In a large bowl, whisk together the flours, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, and salt; set aside. 
3. In another large bowl, use an electric mixer on low to beat together the butter and sugar, then add the eggs and vanilla. Mix on low until combined. Add 1/3 of the flour mixture and beat on low until combined, then add 1/3 of the yogurt and beat on low until combined. Alternate between the two until fully incorporated. 
4. For the crumb topping. Use a fork to whisk together the flour, oats, sugar, cinnamon, and salt. Add the butter and use the back of the fork to mix everything together until crumbly. 
5. Pour half the batter into the pan, evenly spread the cranberry sauce over top, then add remaining batter and smooth with a spatula. 
6. Distribute the crumb topping evenly. 
7. Bake for 60-70 minutes, until a cake tester comes out clean. Remove from the oven and place on a rack to cool completely before removing the sides of the pan and cutting. Dust the top with a bit of powdered sugar before serving. ‚ò∫Ô∏è (üé•: @flovephoto ‚ù§Ô∏è)
